    "body": "### Problem\n\nI found that resizing hover windows does not work even after #32607 in my environment but works on clean Nvim. After bisecting my configs I see that it happens with global `conceallevel` set to `2` (like in LSP utils). As a workaround I added `api.nvim__redraw({win = floating_winnr, valid = true})` after setting `cole` in LSP utils, but not sure what is the correct solution, so not crated PR. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ninit.lua:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('UIEnter', {\n  callback = function ()\n    vim.lsp.start({\n      name = 'luals',\n      cmd = {'lua-language-server'},\n      single_file_support = true,\n    })\n  end\n})\n```\n- `nvim --clean -u init.lua init.lua`\n- wait for loading the server and press `K` on the `function` word and repeat it after `:se cole=2`\n\ncole=0:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1dc94546-b45b-43d1-8a91-5dfcafc6e6bf)\n\ncole=2:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8edbce1b-5316-47b0-8ea0-a1575df00455)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWindow height is set correctly\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1852+g7ead328a48\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDEbian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
