            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It may not be feasible to \"ensure the _on_conceal_line callback cost is only incurred for a window into a buffer where the highlighter may conceal lines.\" only from the C side, which I added to the conceal_lines PR at some point.\n\nRemoving that optimization fixes this issue. We could either:\n1. Remove the optimization; that means always invoking the Lua callback (in windows with `'conceallevel' >= 2`), which _can_ still return early if the active query doesn't have conceal_lines.\n2. Try to invalidate the `wp->w_conceal_line_buf` variable in more cases from C, e.g. when `vim.b.ts_highlight` changes which would resolve the issue here (it's now set _before_ treesitter is started due to plines calls when the window is opened, rather than when the text height is calculated, so `wp->w_conceal_line_provider` is set to false but not invalidated because the buffer didn't change).\n3. Add some API to allow the highlighter to let Nvim know that it wants its `_on_conceal_line` to be invoked, e.g. `vim._decoration_provider_conceal_lines(true)`.\n\nWhat do you think @bfredl?",
